  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious criminal offense with potential legal consequences, which can include:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Potential federal or state prosecution\n- Possible felony charges\n- Substantial fines\n- Prison sentences (often several years)\n\n2. Financial penalties\n- Seizure of laundered assets\n- Monetary fines\n- Potential civil forfeiture\n\n3. Additional consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty finding future employment\n- Potential immigration consequences for non-citizens\n\n4. Potential additional charges\n- Conspiracy\n- Tax evasion\n- Fraud\n- Racketeering\n\nThe specific penalties depend on:\n- Amount of money involved\n- Specific circumstances\n- Prior criminal history\n- Jurisdiction\n- Extent of criminal activity\n\nProsecution and penalties can vary, but money laundering is typically treated as a very serious financial crime with significant legal ramifications.",
